Collections - ArrayList : cumulative

Write a method named cumulative that accepts as a parameter an ArrayList of integers, and modifies it so that each element contains the cumulative sum of the elements up through that index. For example, 
  if the list passed contains {1, 1, 2, 3, 5}, your method should modify it to store {1, 2, 4, 7, 12}.

  public static void cumulative(ArrayList<Integer> list) {
        if(list.isEmpty()) {
            return;
        }
        int sum = list.get(0);
        int size = list.size();
        for(int i = 0; i < size - 1; i++) {
            list.set(i, sum);
            sum += list.get(i + 1);
        }
        list.set(size - 1, sum);
    }

